---
description: Create missing routes only when required by existing flows
globs: ["app/**/*.{ts,tsx}", "src/**/*.{ts,tsx}", "components/**/*.{ts,tsx}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

If an existing screen, button, card, tab, CTA, or action attempts to navigate to a route that does not exist:

Allowed:
- create the missing route
- create the smallest safe screen file needed to satisfy the route
- preserve project routing conventions
- preserve naming consistency with existing routes
- keep the new route implementation minimal and stable

Strictly forbidden:
- do not change the originating button UI
- do not change the layout of the source screen
- do not rename existing routes to avoid creating the missing route
- do not change navigation flow unless required by the missing route fix
- do not create fantasy routes unrelated to existing interactions

When creating a missing route:
- use existing folder conventions
- keep the screen visually simple
- do not introduce a new design system
- do not break tab or stack structure
- do not create broad architecture changes

Default behavior:
create only the minimal missing route required for an existing interaction to function.
